body_text:
@yanivbl6 Thanks for looking into it. There is another sync wrapper function, SetProtoFromGPUSync. We should convert that back to async as well.
The motivation for using sync wrapper is mainly for simplicity. Otherwise, you end up with chained call-backs, which is actually fairly common in tensorflow code.
Please submit a PR if you have a fix.

body:
@yanivbl6 Thanks for looking into it. There is another sync wrapper function, [SetProtoFromGPUSync](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/contrib/verbs/rdma.cc#L730). We should convert that back to async as well. 

The motivation for using sync wrapper is mainly for simplicity. Otherwise, you end up with chained call-backs, which is actually fairly common in tensorflow code.

Please submit a PR if you have a fix.
